msgstr "目錄"

#: ../../algorithms/trpo.rst:10
msgid "Background"
msgstr "背景"

#: ../../algorithms/trpo.rst:12
msgid "(Previously: `Background for VPG`_)"
msgstr "（先前章節：`Background for VPG`_）"

#: ../../algorithms/trpo.rst:16
msgid ""
"TRPO updates policies by taking the largest step possible to improve "
"performance, while satisfying a special constraint on how close the new "
"and old policies are allowed to be. The constraint is expressed in terms "
"of `KL-Divergence`_, a measure of (something like, but not exactly) "
"distance between probability distributions."
msgstr ""
"TRPO 透過在滿足新舊策略之間距離特殊約束的前提下，盡可能邁出最大步伐來改善性"
"能，以此更新策略。該約束以 `KL-Divergence`_（KL 散度）來表示，這是一種衡量機"
"率分佈之間距離（類似但不完全等同於距離）的度量。"

#: ../../algorithms/trpo.rst:18
msgid ""
"This is different from normal policy gradient, which keeps new and old "
"policies close in parameter space. But even seemingly small differences "
"in parameter space can have very large differences in performance---so a "
"single bad step can collapse the policy performance. This makes it "
"dangerous to use large step sizes with vanilla policy gradients, thus "
"hurting its sample efficiency. TRPO nicely avoids this kind of collapse, "
"and tends to quickly and monotonically improve performance."
msgstr ""
"這與一般的策略梯度 (Policy Gradient) 不同，後者是在參數空間中保持新舊策略的接"
"近。但即使在參數空間中看似微小的差異，也可能導致性能上的巨大差異——因此一個錯"
"誤的步驟就可能導致策略性能崩潰。這使得在原始策略梯度中使用大步長變得危險，從"
"而影響其樣本效率。TRPO 很好地避免了這類崩潰，並傾向於快速且單調地改善性能。"

#: ../../algorithms/trpo.rst:23
msgid "Quick Facts"
msgstr "快速概覽"

#: ../../algorithms/trpo.rst:25
msgid "TRPO is an on-policy algorithm."
msgstr "TRPO 是一種同策略 (On-policy) 演算法。"

#: ../../algorithms/trpo.rst:26
msgid ""
"TRPO can be used for environments with either discrete or continuous "
"action spaces."
msgstr "TRPO 可用於具有離散或連續動作空間 (Action Space) 的環境。"

#: ../../algorithms/trpo.rst:27
msgid "The Spinning Up implementation of TRPO supports parallelization with MPI."
msgstr "Spinning Up 的 TRPO 實作支援透過 MPI 進行平行化。"

#: ../../algorithms/trpo.rst:30
msgid "Key Equations"
msgstr "關鍵方程式"

#: ../../algorithms/trpo.rst:32
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Let :math:`\\pi_{\\theta}` denote a policy with parameters "
":math:`\\theta`. The theoretical TRPO update is:"
msgstr ""
"令 :math:`\\pi_{\\theta}` 表示參數為 :math:`\\theta` 的策略。理論上的 "
"TRPO 更新為："

#: ../../algorithms/trpo.rst:34
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"\\theta_{k+1} = \\arg \\max_{\\theta} \\; & {\\mathcal L}(\\theta_k, "
"\\theta) \\\\\n"
"\\text{s.t.} \\; & \\bar{D}_{KL}(\\theta || \\theta_k) \\leq \\delta"
msgstr ""

#: ../../algorithms/trpo.rst:39
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"where :math:`{\\mathcal L}(\\theta_k, \\theta)` is the *surrogate "
"advantage*, a measure of how policy :math:`\\pi_{\\theta}` performs "
"relative to the old policy :math:`\\pi_{\\theta_k}` using data from the "
"old policy:"
msgstr ""
"其中 :math:`{\\mathcal L}(\\theta_k, \\theta)` 是*替代優勢 (Surrogate "
"Advantage)*，用於衡量策略 :math:`\\pi_{\\theta}` 相對於舊策略 "
":math:`\\pi_{\\theta_k}` 的表現，使用來自舊策略的資料："

#: ../../algorithms/trpo.rst:41
msgid ""
"{\\mathcal L}(\\theta_k, \\theta) = \\underE{s,a \\sim \\pi_{\\theta_k}}{"
"\n"
"    \\frac{\\pi_{\\theta}(a|s)}{\\pi_{\\theta_k}(a|s)} "
"A^{\\pi_{\\theta_k}}(s,a)\n"
"    },"
msgstr ""

#: ../../algorithms/trpo.rst:47
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"and :math:`\\bar{D}_{KL}(\\theta || \\theta_k)` is an average KL-"
"divergence between policies across states visited by the old policy:"
msgstr ""
"而 :math:`\\bar{D}_{KL}(\\theta || \\theta_k)` 是舊策略所訪問的狀態上，"
"策略之間的平均 KL 散度："

#: ../../algorithms/trpo.rst:49
msgid ""
"\\bar{D}_{KL}(\\theta || \\theta_k) = \\underE{s \\sim \\pi_{\\theta_k}}{"
"\n"
"    D_{KL}\\left(\\pi_{\\theta}(\\cdot|s) || \\pi_{\\theta_k} (\\cdot|s) "
"\\right)\n"
"}."
msgstr ""

#: ../../algorithms/trpo.rst:55 ../../algorithms/trpo.rst:74
#: ../../algorithms/trpo.rst:157
msgid "You Should Know"
msgstr "你應該知道"

#: ../../algorithms/trpo.rst:57
msgid ""
"The objective and constraint are both zero when :math:`\\theta = "
"\\theta_k`. Furthermore, the gradient of the constraint with respect to "
":math:`\\theta` is zero when :math:`\\theta = \\theta_k`. Proving these "
"facts requires some subtle command of the relevant math---it's an "
"exercise worth doing, whenever you feel ready!"
msgstr ""
"當 :math:`\\theta = \\theta_k` 時，目標函數和約束條件都為零。此外，約束條件對"
" :math:`\\theta` 的梯度在 :math:`\\theta = \\theta_k` 時也為零。證明這些事實"
"需要對相關數學有一定的掌握——這是一個值得做的練習，等你準備好的時候可以試試！"

#: ../../algorithms/trpo.rst:60
msgid ""
"The theoretical TRPO update isn't the easiest to work with, so TRPO makes"
" some approximations to get an answer quickly. We Taylor expand the "
"objective and constraint to leading order around :math:`\\theta_k`:"
msgstr ""
"理論上的 TRPO 更新並不容易直接使用，因此 TRPO 做了一些近似以快速得到結果。"
"我們在 :math:`\\theta_k` 附近對目標函數和約束條件進行 Taylor 展開至首階："

#: ../../algorithms/trpo.rst:62
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"{\\mathcal L}(\\theta_k, \\theta) &\\approx g^T (\\theta - \\theta_k) "
"\\\\\n"
"\\bar{D}_{KL}(\\theta || \\theta_k) & \\approx \\frac{1}{2} (\\theta - "
"\\theta_k)^T H (\\theta - \\theta_k)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../algorithms/trpo.rst:67
msgid "resulting in an approximate optimization problem,"
msgstr "得到一個近似的最佳化問題，"

#: ../../algorithms/trpo.rst:69
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"\\theta_{k+1} = \\arg \\max_{\\theta} \\; & g^T (\\theta - \\theta_k) "
"\\\\\n"
"\\text{s.t.} \\; & \\frac{1}{2} (\\theta - \\theta_k)^T H (\\theta - "
"\\theta_k) \\leq \\delta."
msgstr ""

#: ../../algorithms/trpo.rst:76
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"By happy coincidence, the gradient :math:`g` of the surrogate advantage "
"function with respect to :math:`\\theta`, evaluated at :math:`\\theta = "
"\\theta_k`, is exactly equal to the policy gradient, "
":math:`\\nabla_{\\theta} J(\\pi_{\\theta})`! Try proving this, if you "
"feel comfortable diving into the math."
msgstr ""
"巧合的是，替代優勢函數對 :math:`\\theta` 的梯度 :math:`g`，在 "
":math:`\\theta = \\theta_k` 處求值時，恰好等於策略梯度 "
":math:`\\nabla_{\\theta} J(\\pi_{\\theta})`！如果你對深入數學感到自在，"
"可以試著證明這一點。"

#: ../../algorithms/trpo.rst:78
msgid ""
"This approximate problem can be analytically solved by the methods of "
"Lagrangian duality [1]_, yielding the solution:"
msgstr ""
"這個近似問題可以透過 Lagrangian 對偶方法 [1]_ 解析求解，得到："

#: ../../algorithms/trpo.rst:80
msgid ""
"\\theta_{k+1} = \\theta_k + \\sqrt{\\frac{2 \\delta}{g^T H^{-1} g}} "
"H^{-1} g."
msgstr ""

#: ../../algorithms/trpo.rst:84
msgid ""
"If we were to stop here, and just use this final result, the algorithm "
"would be exactly calculating the `Natural Policy Gradient`_. A problem is"
" that, due to the approximation errors introduced by the Taylor "
"expansion, this may not satisfy the KL constraint, or actually improve "
"the surrogate advantage. TRPO adds a modification to this update rule: a "
"backtracking line search,"
msgstr ""
"如果我們到此為止，直接使用這個最終結果，該演算法就恰好是在計算"
"`Natural Policy Gradient`_（自然策略梯度）。問題在於，由於 Taylor 展開引入的"
"近似誤差，結果可能不滿足 KL 約束，或者無法真正改善替代優勢。TRPO 對此更新規則"
"增加了一個修改：回溯線搜索 (Backtracking Line Search)，"

#: ../../algorithms/trpo.rst:86
msgid ""
"\\theta_{k+1} = \\theta_k + \\alpha^j \\sqrt{\\frac{2 \\delta}{g^T H^{-1}"
" g}} H^{-1} g,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../algorithms/trpo.rst:90
msgid ""
"where :math:`\\alpha \\in (0,1)` is the backtracking coefficient, and "
":math:`j` is the smallest nonnegative integer such that "
":math:`\\pi_{\\theta_{k+1}}` satisfies the KL constraint and produces a "
"positive surrogate advantage."
msgstr ""
"其中 :math:`\\alpha \\in (0,1)` 是回溯係數，:math:`j` 是使得 "
":math:`\\pi_{\\theta_{k+1}}` 滿足 KL 約束並產生正替代優勢的最小非負整數。"

#: ../../algorithms/trpo.rst:92
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Lastly: computing and storing the matrix inverse, :math:`H^{-1}`, is "
"painfully expensive when dealing with neural network policies with "
"thousands or millions of parameters. TRPO sidesteps the issue by using "
"the `conjugate gradient`_ algorithm to solve :math:`Hx = g` for :math:`x "
"= H^{-1} g`, requiring only a function which can compute the matrix-"
"vector product :math:`Hx` instead of computing and storing the whole "
"matrix :math:`H` directly. This is not too hard to do: we set up a "
"symbolic operation to calculate"
msgstr ""
"最後：當處理具有數千或數百萬個參數的神經網路策略時，計算和儲存矩陣逆 "
":math:`H^{-1}` 的代價非常高昂。TRPO 透過使用 `conjugate gradient`_"
"（共軛梯度）演算法來求解 :math:`Hx = g` 以得到 :math:`x = H^{-1} g`，"
"從而迴避了這個問題，只需要一個能計算矩陣-向量乘積 :math:`Hx` 的函式，"
"而不需要直接計算和儲存整個矩陣 :math:`H`。這並不太難實現：我們建立一個符號"
"運算來計算"

#: ../../algorithms/trpo.rst:94
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Hx = \\nabla_{\\theta} \\left( \\left(\\nabla_{\\theta} "
"\\bar{D}_{KL}(\\theta || \\theta_k)\\right)^T x \\right),"
msgstr ""

#: ../../algorithms/trpo.rst:98
msgid "which gives us the correct output without computing the whole matrix."
msgstr "這樣就可以在不計算整個矩陣的情況下得到正確的輸出。"

#: ../../algorithms/trpo.rst:100
msgid ""
"See `Convex Optimization`_ by Boyd and Vandenberghe, especially chapters "
"2 through 5."
msgstr "參見 Boyd 和 Vandenberghe 的 `Convex Optimization`_，特別是第 2 到第 5 章。"

#: ../../algorithms/trpo.rst:108
msgid "Exploration vs. Exploitation"
msgstr "探索與利用"

#: ../../algorithms/trpo.rst:110
msgid ""
"TRPO trains a stochastic policy in an on-policy way. This means that it "
"explores by sampling actions according to the latest version of its "
"stochastic policy. The amount of randomness in action selection depends "
"on both initial conditions and the training procedure. Over the course of"
" training, the policy typically becomes progressively less random, as the"
" update rule encourages it to exploit rewards that it has already found. "
"This may cause the policy to get trapped in local optima."
msgstr ""
"TRPO 以同策略的方式訓練一個隨機策略 (Stochastic Policy)。這意味著它透過根據"
"最新版本的隨機策略取樣動作來進行探索 (Exploration)。動作選擇的隨機程度取決於"
"初始條件和訓練過程。在訓練過程中，策略通常會逐漸變得不那麼隨機，因為更新規則"
"會鼓勵它利用 (Exploitation) 已經發現的獎勵。這可能導致策略陷入局部最優解 "
"(Local Optima)。"

#: ../../algorithms/trpo.rst:114
msgid "Pseudocode"
msgstr "虛擬碼"

#: ../../algorithms/trpo.rst:116
msgid ""
"\\begin{algorithm}[H]\n"
"    \\caption{Trust Region Policy Optimization}\n"
"    \\label{alg1}\n"
"\\begin{algorithmic}[1]\n"
"    \\STATE Input: initial policy parameters $\\theta_0$, initial value "
"function parameters $\\phi_0$\n"
"    \\STATE Hyperparameters: KL-divergence limit $\\delta$, backtracking "
"coefficient $\\alpha$, maximum number of backtracking steps $K$\n"
"    \\FOR{$k = 0,1,2,...$}\n"
"    \\STATE Collect set of trajectories ${\\mathcal D}_k = \\{\\tau_i\\}$"
" by running policy $\\pi_k = \\pi(\\theta_k)$ in the environment.\n"
"    \\STATE Compute rewards-to-go $\\hat{R}_t$.\n"
"    \\STATE Compute advantage estimates, $\\hat{A}_t$ (using any method "
"of advantage estimation) based on the current value function "
"$V_{\\phi_k}$.\n"
"    \\STATE Estimate policy gradient as\n"
"        \\begin{equation*}\n"
"        \\hat{g}_k = \\frac{1}{|{\\mathcal D}_k|} \\sum_{\\tau \\in "
"{\\mathcal D}_k} \\sum_{t=0}^T \\left. \\nabla_{\\theta} "
"\\log\\pi_{\\theta}(a_t|s_t)\\right|_{\\theta_k} \\hat{A}_t.\n"
"        \\end{equation*}\n"
"    \\STATE Use the conjugate gradient algorithm to compute\n"
"        \\begin{equation*}\n"
"        \\hat{x}_k \\approx \\hat{H}_k^{-1} \\hat{g}_k,\n"
"        \\end{equation*}\n"
"        where $\\hat{H}_k$ is the Hessian of the sample average KL-"
"divergence.\n"
"    \\STATE Update the policy by backtracking line search with\n"
"        \\begin{equation*}\n"
"        \\theta_{k+1} = \\theta_k + \\alpha^j \\sqrt{ "
"\\frac{2\\delta}{\\hat{x}_k^T \\hat{H}_k \\hat{x}_k}} \\hat{x}_k,\n"
"        \\end{equation*}\n"
"        where $j \\in \\{0, 1, 2, ... K\\}$ is the smallest value which "
"improves the sample loss and satisfies the sample KL-divergence "
"constraint.\n"
"    \\STATE Fit value function by regression on mean-squared error:\n"
"        \\begin{equation*}\n"
"        \\phi_{k+1} = \\arg \\min_{\\phi} \\frac{1}{|{\\mathcal D}_k| T} "
"\\sum_{\\tau \\in {\\mathcal D}_k} \\sum_{t=0}^T\\left( V_{\\phi} (s_t) -"
" \\hat{R}_t \\right)^2,\n"
"        \\end{equation*}\n"
"        typically via some gradient descent algorithm.\n"
"    \\ENDFOR\n"
"\\end{algorithmic}\n"
"\\end{algorithm}"
msgstr ""

